Summary: A white, possibly oval-shaped object with a short blue wing on either side of object hovering east of I-135. Started moving slowly like a blimp and then took off and disappeared.
divs: Sighting DetailsI was wondering if you heard of any sightings over Wichita late Friday afternoon between 4-5pm? I was driving south on I-135 and to my left there was what appeared to be an oval-shaped object, white, with a blue "wing" or "fin" to either side. My eyes could have been playing tricks on me but my wife also noted that it was just hovering for a minute and when we circled around to see what it was it was moving upward at about 30-35 degrees, gaining speed until it just disappeared. My wife said that it had to have been a blimp but I never heard of a blimp that flew that high up in the air. We weren't the only ones who saw it. Several cars on 135 slowed down to look at it.
